-- Property drives Mauritius conglomerate Rogers' full-yr profit
-- By Jean Paul Arouff
-- Thu Sep 04, 2014 11:17AM EDT
-- None



PORT LOUIS, Sept 4 (Reuters) - Mauritian conglomerate Rogers <ROGE.MZ> reported full-year pretax profit of 807 million Mauritius rupees ($26.12 million) on Thursday, driven by its property and financial services units.

The group - which operates in the Indian Ocean island's financial, property, hotel, aviation and logistics sectors - changed its reporting period to June 30. It said pretax profit in the previous nine months to June 30 was 1.95 billion rupees. Revenue for the period was 6.1 billion rupees and earnings per share were 17.67 rupees, Rogers said.